JOHANNESBURG Phakamani Mahlambi, Luther Singh and Diamond Thopola will make their Bafana Bafana debut when they start against Angola in an international friendly match at Buffalo City Stadium in East London on Tuesday night.The three are part of the nine changes made by stand-in Bafana Bafana head coach Owen da Gama from the team that notched up the 3-1 victory over Guinea-Bissau in Durban on Saturday.Defenders Erick Mathoho and Tebogo Langerman are the only survivors from the last match.Da Gama makes wholesale changes for Angola clash, Jali captain https://t.co/5Q77hq4RcgDarren Keet gets the nod in goals.His last game for Bafana Bafana was the 3-1 loss to Algeria in January 2015 in the Africa Cup of Nations tournament held in Equatorial Guinea.Langerman will continue at left-back while Thopola will occupy the right-back position.Mathoho will partner with Rivaldo Coetzee in central defence.Andile Jali and Tiyani Mabunda pull the strings from the middle of the park, where they will be assisted by Under-20 internationals Mahlambi and Singh.Jali will captain the side the second time he has done so.READ: Teenage Mahlambi eyeing Bafana debutHe last wore the armband in January 2015 in Libreville, Gabon when Bafana Bafana defeated Mali 3-0 in a pre-tournament friendly for the 2015 Africa Cup of Nations.The Belgium-based player has shrugged off a shoulder injury to fight his way into the starting lineup.Upfront, Lebohang Manyama will go in search of goals alongside Percy Tau.The injured Thulani Hlatshwayo will be in the stands and will be joined by Thabo Mnyamane as only 12 players are allowed to sit on the bench.Bafana Bafana XI: Darren Keet (GK), Diamond Thopola, Tebogo Langerman, Erick Mathoho, Rivaldo Coetzee, Andile Jali (captain), Tiyani Mabunda, Phakamani Mahlambi, Luther Singh, Lebohang Manyama, Percy Tau.Substitutes: Shu-aib Walters (GK), Itumeleng Khune (GK), Lorenzo Gordinho, Ramahlwe Mphahlele, Hlompo Kekana, Kamohelo Mokotjo, Dean Furman, Keagan Dolly, Themba Zwane, Thulani Serero, Lars Veldwijk, Kermit Erasmus.African News Agency